# Genaan E-Commerce: System Architecture & API Blueprint

This document serves as a complete structural overview of the **Genaan** administrative backend and E-Commerce platform architecture. It is designed to be fully reproducible when binding a front-end interface, deploying a headless system, or porting core operations to another project.

---

## 1. Technology Stack
* **Framework:** Laravel (PHP)
* **Design Pattern:** MVC (Model-View-Controller)
* **Frontend Tools (Admin):** Blade Templating Engine, TailwindCSS via CDN, Chart.js, Google Material Icons.
* **Database:** MySQL relational tracking.

---

## 2. Database Schema (Schema Topography)

The database spans heavily typed relational tables mapped precisely for complex e-commerce functions.

### Core User & Access Hierarchy
* `users`: Defines authenticatable properties, extended with basic tracking (`is_admin`, `last_login_at`, `provider`).
* `roles` & `user_roles`: Pivot mapping allowing multi-dimensional privilege bindings.
* `addresses`: Relates back to a `user_id` mapping normalized location delivery data and `is_default` booleans.

### Operational Catalog
* `categories`: Hierarchical (`parent_id`) allowing deeply nested parent/child relationships.
* `products`: Base catalog items. Constrained by literal specific `enum('type')` variants: `plant`, `pot`, `soil`, `vitamin`, `accessory`.
* `product_variants`: Optional pricing and explicit base stock overrides.
* `product_attributes`: Dynamic key-value descriptors (`attribute_key`, `attribute_value`).
* `product_images`: 1:Many relationships allowing carousel galleries.
* `plant_care`: Dedicated AI/UI helper schema parsing optimal `watering_days`, `light_level`, and `humidity_level`.

### Inventory State Engine
* `inventory`: Central ledger tying `product_id`/`variant_id` to current `quantity` offsets and actively `reserved` (e.g. frozen in checkout) quantities.
* `inventory_logs`: Time-series ledger marking every physical movement with an enum `type` (`in`, `out`, `reserve`, `release`, `adjustment`).

### Cart & Checkout Matrix
* `carts` & `cart_items`: Volatile session-ledgers mapping to `user_id` bounds.
* `orders`: Generates immutable checkout footprints recording `subtotal`, `discount`, `total`, `status`, and `payment_status` mapping linearly to an `address_id` state.
* `order_items`: Maps literal finalized prices bridging product gaps securely.
* `order_events`: Extensible hook registering post-purchase timelines (e.g., dispatched, in-transit webhooks).

### Engagement & Marketing
* `coupons`: Marketing layer evaluating percent/fixed constraints conditionally mapped through total usage ceilings and `min_order` gates.
* `reviews`: 1->5 stars relational binding traversing user and product models explicitly.
* `posts`: CMS binding facilitating article or blog broadcasts directly onto the storefront.

### System Globals & Insight Tracking
* `settings`: Agnostic application key-value pair strings regulating UI logic operations (e.g., `stock_alert_threshold`, `currency`).
* `audit_logs` & `analytics_events`: Traceability arrays bridging custom UX tracking and security tracking metadata.

---

## 3. Server Logic & API Controllers

The administration layer utilizes singular `ManagementControllers` mapping to specific database responsibilities seamlessly integrating metrics computation.

### `DashboardController`
Serves as the highest-level operational read-node. Centralizes cross-functional metrics.
* **Retrieves:** Total revenue constraints (where paid), global user footprint counts, and active order counts.
* **Analytics Compute:** Pipes JSON array groupings formatting `Activity Logs`, `Sales By Day` 30-day lookbacks, and dynamic `Top Product` matrix revenue comparisons grouped by `SUM(oi.quantity * p.price)`.

### `ProductManagementController`
Curates the entire retail catalog layer while securely cross-calculating inventory counts.
* Executes index filtering with `like` matchings mapping names or scientific identities.
* Aggregates live unfulfilled quantities evaluating against dynamic `settings` thresholds, exposing instant low-stock indicators to admins.

### `InventoryManagementController` / `ProcurementController`
Tracks inbound/outbound financial metrics.
* Uses aggregate SQL triggers grouping `Stock Inventory Counts -> Category Bounds`.
* Provides placeholder evaluation UI bounds exposing forecasted budget allocation formulas and "Supplier Fulfillment" percentages based purely on logic matrices.

### `OrderManagementController`
* Maps REST interfaces tracking state machine changes. Captures `PUT /orders/{id}/status` payloads safely converting state from `pending -> confirmed -> shipped`. 

### `CustomerManagementController`
* Queries `users` securely enforcing UI limits to `is_admin = false`. 
* Uses advanced select operations running `DB::table('orders')->selectRaw()` grouping lifetime spends and indexing them immediately to the users array.

### `SupportChatController`
Handles the backend synchronization of a live user/admin inbox framework.
* Fetches relational message cascades conditionally parsing ascending timestamps.
* Exposes functional action targets marking thread reads globally.

### `SettingsManagementController`
Handles the platform configurations explicitly writing rows via un-restricted loops against `Setting::updateOrCreate()`. Handles secure password resetting validation bounds securely isolated from settings keys.

---

## 4. Frontend Route Definitions (Web REST Interfaces)

The HTTP pathways are statically shielded by global `auth` and `admin` middleware gates isolating data bounds globally.

* **Overview & Aggregation:**
  * `GET /admin/dashboard`: Global aggregation core matrix routing. (Legacy points `/admin/analytics` safely 301 redirected here).

* **Inventory & Catalog Flow:**
  * `GET /admin/products`: Base catalog listing and active stock thresholds. (Legacy points `/admin/inventory` safely 301 redirected here).
  * `GET/POST /admin/products/create`: Standardized form handler initializing basic elements and mapping dynamic slugs implicitly.
  * `PUT/DELETE /admin/products/{product}`: Item update routines.
  * `GET /admin/procurement`: Forecast tracking UI.

* **Fulfillment Flow:**
  * `GET /admin/orders`: Global order tracker.
  * `GET /admin/orders/{id}`: Detailed transaction receipt rendering item and address bindings.
  * `PUT /admin/orders/{id}/status`: Mutation endpoint locking transaction stages securely.

* **Customer Operations Flow:**
  * `GET /admin/customers`: User query layer sorting lifetime conversion margins.
  * `GET/POST/DELETE /admin/coupons`: Complete marketing creation tools toggling active boolean states.
  * `GET/POST /admin/chats`: Conversation listener bridging real-time text replies back to user profiles.
  
* **Configuration Flow:**
  * `GET /admin/settings`: Settings read pipeline.
  * `POST /admin/settings`: General configuration updates logic trigger.
  * `POST /admin/settings/password`: Authorized password rotation handler.
